        <mxCell id="OKUUgE-HB8_flXC8L4DE-17" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;fontStyle=1;fontSize=20;" value="&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;These four tools are designed to work together as a complete Kubernetes delivery platform, not as standalone replacements for each other:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="70" width="920" x="-510" y="810" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="OKUUgE-HB8_flXC8L4DE-18" parent="1" style="whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 20px;&quot;&gt;If you want a complete CI/CD system, you need both Argo Events and Argo Workflows — Events processes triggers from GitHub/GitLab and creates Workflows, which clone repos, build, test, and push changes. Argo CD then picks up those changes and rolls them out. Argo Rollouts handles the deployment strategy itself.&lt;/font&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="250" width="1090" x="-510" y="1000" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="OKUUgE-HB8_flXC8L4DE-19" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;fontSize=20;" value="&lt;strong&gt;Argo CD&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;em&gt;deploy&lt;/em&gt; your app from Git (the CD part, the most popular by far)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="100" width="480" x="-500" y="-110" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="YOhPZaCioL1XJX9fttwe-1" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 20px;&quot;&gt;Argo Workflows — build and run multi-step jobs, CI pipelines, ML tasks&lt;/font&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="390" x="70" y="-90" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="YOhPZaCioL1XJX9fttwe-2" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 20px;&quot;&gt;Argo Events — listen and trigger — the glue that reacts to GitHub, SQS, schedules, etc.&lt;/font&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="55" width="430" x="610" y="-87.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
